evidence: A novel equiatomic TiNbTaZrMo high-entropy alloy (HEA) was developed as a new metallic biomaterial.
The as-cast and annealed TiNbTaZrMo HEAs show a high σ 0.2 of N1000 MPa. The values of σ 0.2 in the TiNbTaZrMo HEAs are higher than those of the refractory TiNbTaZrHf HEA and Ti-6Al-4V alloys.
